<!-- TOPICS -->
<section class="topics-section">
  <div class="main-container">
    <div class="section-header" style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">
      <span class="section-label">Speaking Topics</span>
      <div class="section-rule"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="topics-grid">

      <div class="topic-card">
        <span class="topic-number">01</span>
        <h3 class="topic-title">Leading Through Uncertainty</h3>
        <p class="topic-hook">The world cannot be controlled. Leaders who accept that truth — and learn to navigate rather than command — are the ones who endure. This is the through-line of <em>Chasing Lights</em>.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="topic-card">
        <span class="topic-number">02</span>
        <h3 class="topic-title">Desire Lines and What They Reveal</h3>
        <p class="topic-hook">Paths form where people actually walk, not where planners intend. The same is true of capital, cities, and culture. A framework for reading trends, investment flows, urbanism, and sustainability through the lens of desire lines.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="topic-card">
        <span class="topic-number">03</span>
        <h3 class="topic-title">Innovation and Change Management</h3>
        <p class="topic-hook">Change is rarely comfortable, and the organizations that survive it aren't the ones that embraced it most eagerly — they're the ones that understood the painful, human process of getting there.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="topic-card">
        <span class="topic-number">04</span>
        <h3 class="topic-title">Storytelling and Meaning in a Fragmented World</h3>
        <p class="topic-hook">We are drowning in information and starving for meaning. The ideas behind <em>Chasing Lights</em> and the AFIRE Podcast — on why long-form reflection, narrative, and human connection still matter deeply.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="topic-card">
        <span class="topic-number">05</span>
        <h3 class="topic-title">Why Globalism Still Matters</h3>
        <p class="topic-hook">Cross-border investment, the experience of being a foreigner, belonging across cultures — and why the connective tissue of a globalized world, however frayed, remains worth preserving and defending.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

