<!-- BIO + TESTIMONIAL -->
<main class="main-container">
  <section class="bio-section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="section-label">About Gunnar</span>
      <div class="section-rule"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="bio-grid">
      <div class="bio-text">
        <h2>A career at the intersection of ideas, investment, and leadership</h2>
        <p>Gunnar Branson has spent more than three decades in commercial real estate, professional services, and association leadership — most recently as CEO of AFIRE, the association for international real estate investors, whose members represent nearly $4 trillion in U.S. real estate assets under management across 24 countries. Before that, he served as CEO of NAREIM and led strategy, innovation, and marketing for Fortune 500 and mid-market companies.</p>
        <p>As host of the award-winning AFIRE Podcast and publisher of the AFIRE Summit Journal, Gunnar has spent years in conversation with the world's leading investors, economists, urbanists, and geopolitical thinkers — distilling ideas that matter into insights that move people to act.</p>
        <p>He is also the author of <em>Chasing Lights</em>, a memoir-in-essays about growing up in Alaska, finding belonging across borders, and learning to lead in a world that resists control. Gunnar's background in drama and storytelling — combined with his decades of boardroom and stage experience — makes him a speaker who is equally at home with data and metaphor, with the global and the deeply personal.</p>
        <a href="https://gunnarbranson.com/about/" class="read-more" style="margin-top: 0.5rem;">Full Biography &rarr;</a>
      </div>

      <div>
        <div class="testimonial-block">
          <blockquote>"A rare combination of intellect, character and charm — Gunnar draws upon his many interests and experiences to create new insights and develop truly innovative solutions."</blockquote>
          <cite>— Professional endorsement, LinkedIn</cite>
        </div>

        <div class="quote-block" style="margin-bottom: 0; text-align: left; padding: 2rem 2.5rem;">
          <blockquote style="font-size: 1.1rem;">"At a certain age, it becomes tempting to believe that the light is behind you. But there is always more light ahead."</blockquote>
          <cite>— Gunnar Branson, <em>Chasing Lights</em></cite>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
